# QA AUDIT AGENT — CIRRA STANDARD
# Universal — no project-specific changes needed
# Agent 2 trigger line: "QA AUDIT — run full combined audit
# on the brief that just completed. Read all files in the
# last git commit before starting."

## MANDATORY PRE-AUDIT READS
Before auditing, read every file touched in the last git commit.
Run: git diff HEAD~1 --name-only
Read each file in full before issuing any verdict.

## 20-POINT AUDIT CHECKLIST

### SECURITY
1. No service role key in src/ anywhere
2. No PII logged to console or Sentry
3. RLS enabled on every new table
4. No auth bypass in any new function
5. No secrets in committed files

### ARCHITECTURE
6. Single Supabase client only
7. Single AuthProvider only
8. No naked any types
9. No duplicate imports or redundant abstractions
10. SECURITY DEFINER used correctly on all RPC functions

### UI COMPLETENESS
11. Loading state handled on every async operation
12. Empty state handled on every list/table
13. Error state handled and visible to user
14. Disabled state on all buttons during async ops

### PERFORMANCE
15. No N+1 queries in hooks or components
16. Realtime subscriptions scoped — not SELECT *
17. Indexes exist on all FK columns and filter columns
18. No unnecessary re-renders from missing dependencies

### STATE MACHINE
19. No raw status string writes — use RPC or typed enum
20. Terminal states are terminal — no transitions out

### TYPES
Run and report result of each:
- tsc --noEmit
- npm run build
- npm audit --audit-level=high

## VERDICT
Must be one of:
PASS TO DEPLOY — all 20 points green, build clean
BLOCKED — list every failing point with file and line number

No partial verdicts. No "mostly good." PASS or BLOCKED.
